






HOME




























 



























Bay Capital is an active fiduciary. However,  we invest the way we want our capital to be managed — with the utmost care. In the private equity business, we source our own deals by offering strategic inputs for our investees and in the process become trusted advisors.  This creates a long-term relationship and, often, an attractive entry price. In investing in public markets, we look for companies with moats that are incredibly difficult to breach. Our typical holding period is quite long – creating overall cost efficiencies.  We are motivated by generating performance and our overarching philosophy is to always keep our investors’ interest ahead of our own.








WHO WE ARE
—








 

Established team with over 100 years of experience
We are shareholders alongside our investors
The investment management firm focuses primarily on companies based in India








 
 
 
A BOUTIQUE INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT FIRM
—








 
 
WELL ESTABLISHED OPERATIONS IN INDIA MAURITIUS & SINGAPORE
—







 

Regulated by SEBI (India), MAS (Singapore), and FSC (Mauritius)
Both long-only and private equity businesses share operational, compliance, and marketing resources










 
 
LONG TRACK RECORD IN PRIVATE EQUITY
—







 
 



17 deals completed on a deal by deal basis
Recent exits include McDonald’s India (Westlife), Vini Cosmetics, and Sterling Holiday Resorts













 
EXTENSIVE TRACK RECORD IN LONG-ONLY, PUBLIC MARKETS INVESTING IN INDIA
—







 
 
 
 

Concentrated, bottom-up, long-only approach


Local network providing quality, accuracy, and transparency for an information advantage













Investing in India today reminds me of the US in 1982: double-digit interest rates beginning to fall, a successful central bank fighting inflation and much needed labor reforms being implemented. However, there is one important difference. India's GDP/Capita in 2014 is equal to that of the US in 1880.”

- James Sheridan, Partner








OUR EDGE
—












FOCUSED APPROACH
—
In our long-only efforts, we are only interested in great companies that have sustainably high ROICs. In the PE business, we invest only in those companies where we believe we can add value to the sponsor while making money for investors









LOCAL PRESENCE
—
Intense research, due diligence and logistic support possible


















EXPERIENCE
—
We believe we have the experience to assist our companies and the judgment to assess sustainability of returns











PATIENCE
—

In our long-only business, we believe in an ‘equity yield curve’ where returns increase with time and therefore seek investors who share our belief in the power of compounding

 

Our PE investments are financed on a deal by deal basis. We never rush to invest committed capital. This patient approach gives us a significant advantage over traditional PE funds
















Private Equity investing in India is filled with challenges.  Bay Capital recognises this and has altered its approach.  First, we never participate in auctions, we source our own deals.  Second, we invest only on a deal by deal basis (usually after long periods of building trust with sponsors).  We therefore feel no pressure to invest based on the cycle of PE fundraising and investing.  We believe this discipline ensures a stable, reliable, investment process and return to our investors.”

 
— Siddharth Mehta, Founder
















 







 
 
ALL INVESTMENTS FINANCED ‘DEAL BY DEAL’
Two benefits: We are in no rush to invest before the end of ‘an investment period’ and secondly, this allows increased transparency for investors.













 
 
CREATE INVESTMENT OPPORTUNITIES FOR OURSELVES
We don't participate in auctions 












 
OUR GOAL IS TO BECOME A LONG-TERM TRUSTED ADVISOR BY OFFERING STRATEGIC INPUT AND UNIQUE SOLUTIONS TO OUR INVESTEES
 






 
 
 
WILLING AND ABLE TO TAKE MANAGEMENT CONTROL
 












 
 
SEVERAL RECENT PROFITABLE EXITS IN A DIFFICULT PERIOD





OUR PRIVATE EQUITY STRATEGY
—














We have found that the best Indian listed businesses have turned India’s ‘idiosyncrasies’  of weak logistics and multiple languages/cultures into significant barriers to entry. Our companies have sustainably high returns by capitalizing on branding, technology and distribution advantages, often built over long periods of time.”

 
— Puneet Saraogi, Co-Founder & Managing Partner, Bay Capital Partners LLP















 







 
 
LONG ONLY PUBLIC EQUITIES
 






 











 
 
CONCENTRATED APPROACH
(15-20 stocks)
 
 












 
 
INTEND TO BE MARKET-CAP AGNOSTIC
 






 
 
FOCUS ON COMPANIES WITH SUSTAINABLY HIGH RETURN ON CAPITAL (ROCE)












 
LOW TURNOVER
Positive implications for expense ratio and for long-term taxable investors
 





OUR LONG-ONLY STRATEGY
—




















Let us combine ‘Look East’ with ‘Link West’ and with our global vision, we can provide a new platform for our economic structure”

 
 Narendra Modi, Prime Minister of India
'Make in India' launch, September 25, 2014







You will see India as a country of opportunities, unmatched across the world. India can be a role model of growth and cohesiveness for the rest of the world."

 
