OUR TEAM
—









 
PUBLIC MARKETS TEAM
—









PUNEET SARAOGI
Based in Mumbai, Puneet is the Co-Founder and Managing Partner of Bay Capital Partners LLP. He has over 8 years of experience.
 
Prior to Bay Capital, he was the Head of the India office of Arisaig Partners; one of the largest Asia focused public funds with investments totaling approximately USD1.5 billion in the Indian sub-continent. He spent seven years with Arisaig and in his last role, he was the Co-Manager of the firm’s Global Emerging Markets Fund which is a USD400mn portfolio.
 
Puneet is an Electronics Engineer from Rajasthan University and an MBA in Finance from XLRI Jamshedpur, India. He has also completed an executive course from Babson, USA.









PRACHI KODIKAL
Based in Mumbai, Prachi is an Investment Analyst at Bay Capital Partners LLP.  She has nine years of experience in Equity Research.
 
Prior to Bay Capital, Prachi worked with Vinya Capital, a boutique investment management firm and Edelweis Securities, one of the largest domestic brokerage houses.
 
Prachi holds a Master’s degree in Management Studies and Bachelors in Commerce from the University of Mumbai.









RAVI SRIVASTAVA
Based in Mumbai,  Ravi  is an Investment Analyst at Bay Capital Partners LLP. He has over five years of professional experience in strategy & decision consulting, investment analysis, and mergers and acquisitions.
 
Prior to Bay Capital, he worked as an Engagement Manager with Singapore based strategy consulting firm SLC . In this position, he led several engagements with clients across India, Asia-Pacific and US. Prior to SLC, he was part of the Mergers & Acquisitions team of Siva Group in India.
 
Ravi is an Electronics & Communication Engineer from NIT, Nagpur and has an MBA from The Indian Institute of Management, Ahmedabad (IIM A).









NISHAD KARKARE
Based in Mumbai,  Nishad  is an Investment Analyst at Bay Capital Partners LLP. He has over five years of professional experience in investment analysis. Prior to Bay Capital, he worked as an Investment Analyst with Singular Capital, an investment management firm and with the wholesale asset management platform of Edelweiss Financial Services.
 
Nishad has an M.Sc. in Physics from Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur (IIT KGP) and an MBA from Indian Institute of Management, Ahmedabad (IIM A).




 
OPERATIONS & COMPLIANCE TEAM
—









BHAVESH SHAH
Based in Singapore, Bhavesh is the Vice President of Bay Capital Partners Pte. Ltd. and has approximately eight years of operational experience.
 
Prior to Bay Capital, he was with Globe Op Financial Services where he was responsible for pricing OTC derivative products.
 
Bhavesh holds a Master’s Degree in Finance from ICFAI and a Master’s Degree in Commerce from the University of Mumbai. Bhavesh is also a Chartered Financial Analyst from ICFAI.









PRAVIN NAIR
Based in Mauritius, Pravin is a Manager at Bay Capital Partners Limited and has over 9 years of experience in Fund Operations.
 
Prior to joining Bay Capital, he worked with SS&C Globe Op Financial Services, where he was involved in the OTC Derivatives Portfolio pricing and operations for major Hedge Fund clients from both the United States and United Kingdom.
 
Pravin holds a Masters Degree in Financial Management and Bachelors Degree in Commerce from the University of Mumbai.









NUSHRAT RAMJAUN
Based in Mauritius, Nushrat is a Junior Manager at Bay Capital Partners Limited.  She has over 7 years of experience in the administration of funds as well as in asset management. Nushrat is currently actively involved in the provision of day-to-day administration of Bay Capital Partners Funds and accounts preparation.
 
Prior to joining Bay Capital, she worked at Bramer Asset Management Ltd. for approximately 5 years where she headed the Administration Team in the Discretionary Portfolio Management Department.
 
Nushrat holds a degree in Finance with Law from the University of Mauritius and a diploma in Trust Creation Law & Practice from STEP.









SUSHMA AMIN
Based in Mumbai, Sushma is the Executive Vice President - Accounts & Finance for Bay Capital Investment Managers Pvt. Ltd. She has approximately 14 years of experience, over 7 of which were in capital markets & asset management at Bay Capital Investment Managers Pvt. Ltd. (Bay Capital).She has been a part of Bay Capital since its inception and was part of the core team that was responsible for the overall Operations, Finance and Compliance functions.
 
Prior to joining Bay Capital, she worked with the Accounts & Finance Department at Responsive Industries as an Accounts Manager.
 
Sushma holds MBA in Finance from Narsee Monjee Institute of Management Studies (NMIMS) and Master’s Degree in Commerce from the University of Mumbai.









Megha Indulkar
Based in Mumbai, Megha is the Accounts Executive at Bay Capital Investment Managers Pvt. Ltd. She has over 13 year’s of experience in the field of  Accounts & Finance.
 
Prior to joining Bay Capital, she was the  Accounts Executive in Responsive Industries Limited. She has also previously held positions at  Ekta World Pvt. Ltd.
 
Megha holds a Bachelor of Commerce degree from the University of Mumbai and completed her Software Application Computers Course through NIIT  in Mumbai.




 
PRIVATE EQUITY TEAM
—









SIDDHARTH MEHTA
Based in Singapore, Siddharth (Sid) is the Founder of Bay Capital. He has had a career spanning over 12 years in asset management.
 
Prior to Bay Capital, Sid was Vice President of Kotak Mahindra UK and was responsible for building Kotak’s international institutional asset management franchise in Europe. Prior to joining Kotak, he was an Executive Director at Gerken Capital Associates (GCA), and established together with the Kotak Mahindra Group “WM India Fund”, one of the first India focused hedge funds.
 
Sid holds a bachelor’s degree in Business Management and Finance from King’s College, University of London. He currently serves on the Boards of Directors of IL&FS Investment Managers, (the largest private equity firm in India), and IL&FS Energy Development Company Ltd.









NIKUNJ DOSHI
Based in Mumbai, Nikunj is a Director at Bay Capital Investment Managers Pvt. Ltd. He has over 25 years of professional experience of which the last 22 years have been in equity research and advisory functions.
 
Prior to Bay Capital, Nikunj was with the portfolio management / asset management division of the Kotak Mahindra Group for over 5 years where he held positions of portfolio analyst, portfolio advisor and fund manager for various concentrated/diversified funds, particularly on the mid-market / thematic space.
 
Nikunj is an Electronics Engineer from M. S. University, Baroda and holds an MBA from the University of Mumbai.









SIVARAMAKRISHNAN S. IYER
Based in Mumbai, Mr. Sivaramakrishnan (Siva) S. Iyer has been associated with Bay Capital Investment Managers Pvt. Ltd. since inception. He advises Bay Capital on various matters.
 
After an initial stint with J M Financial & Investment, he started his career as an Independent Consultant and has over two decades of experience in the field of Management Accounts & Audit, Business Advisory Services and Corporate Finance.
 
Throughout his career, he has advised Small & Medium Enterprises on Capital structuring, Fund raising, Mergers & Acquisition, Capital Market related issues, Financial Diligence, Financial & Business strategy, etc.
 
Siva is a Commerce graduate from the University of Mumbai and qualified as a Chartered Accountant in November 1987.









RAHUL KUMAR JHA
Based in Mumbai, Rahul is an Investment Analyst at Bay Capital Investment Managers Pvt. Ltd. He has over four years of professional experience in consulting and private equity.
 
Prior to Bay Capital, Rahul was part of the Alternative Assets division of the Kotak Mahindra Group. Prior to Kotak Realty,  he was with HSBC in their model risk team. He has also worked with multiple startups as a consultant.
 
Rahul holds an MBA from the Indian Institute of Management (IIM) Calcutta and a Bachelors degree in Electrical Engineering from Indian Institute of Technology (IIT Kanpur). He has also qualified two levels of CFA (USA).




 
BUSINESS TEAM
—









JAMES SHERIDAN
Based in London, James (Jim) has 30 years of experience in the securities and investment management business. He started his career at Goldman Sachs in 1982 as a sales associate in U.S. Shares Sales in New York. He was promoted to Co-Head of US Shares and later moved to Hong Kong to Co-Head the Asian Shares. He was named a Partner and Managing Director in 1996 and in 1999 he was named Head of the Equities Division in Asia.
 
While working in Asia he represented Goldman Sachs in their Indian joint venture initiative with Kotak Securities from 1996-1999.
 
Jim graduated from Brown University with a Bachelor of Science degree in Economics and Applied Mathematics and received an MBA from New York University's Stern School. He has been investing in India since 2007 and is an LP in several Bay Capital Investments. He is the Chair of the Global Fund for Children in Washington, DC.




 
ADMINISTRATIVE TEAM
—









KEYUR MAJMUDAR
Based in Mumbai, Keyur is a Director at Bay Capital Investment Managers and has 18 years of experience in financial services.
 
Prior to joining Bay Capital, he was with the Kotak Mahindra group till 2010 with roles across diverse functions. Keyur was Head of the Non-Discretionary Portfolio Management business for Private Clients and Family Offices at Kotak Securities.  Earlier on, he was based in London with Kotak Mahindra UK Ltd, here he was responsible for both institutional and private client origination and advisory for the offshore asset management business. Keyur started his career with Lazard Credit Capital (the joint venture partner of Lazard Brothers in India), Mumbai.
 
He has a Bachelor’s degree in Commerce from Sydenham College, Mumbai and a Masters in Management from Boston University.









NERISSA GONSALVES
Based in Mumbai, Nerissa is an Executive Assistant at Bay Capital Investment Managers Pvt. Ltd. She  has over 13 year’s of experience in the field of secretarial and administration.
 
Prior to joining Bay Capital, she was the Executive Assistant to the Managing Director of Tata Teleservices Limited. She has also previously held positions at Edelweiss Capital and Elara Capital.
 
Nerissa holds a Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of Mumbai and completed her Secretarial Course through Davar's College in Mumbai.









VAREENA D'SILVA
Based in Mumbai, Vareena is an Executive Assistant at Bay Capital Partners LLP. and has over ten years of experience in the Financial Services industry.
 
Prior to joining Bay Capital, she worked in the Human Resources Department at Kotak Mahindra Bank as a Relationship Manager for Pan India employees.
 
Vareena holds a Bachelor’s of Arts degree majoring in  Economics from the University of Mumbai and a Post Graduate Diploma in Human Resources from Narsee Monjee Institute of Management Studies (NMIMS).




 













