 Flexible Capital
 for the Lower Middle Market








Bay Capital Investment Partners


Capital for the Lower Middle Market
 Bay Capital Investment Partners specifically addresses the capital needs of smaller U.S. companies by providing senior debt, subordinated debt, mezzanine capital and equity capital to facilitate acquisitions, management buyouts and recapitalizations  and to provide growth capital.


Structuring Solutions
Smaller companies generally require more financing flexibility than many banks can provide, and such companies often cannot access larger private equity funds or other financing sources. Bay Capital offers a creative, flexible approach to structuring funding solutions for the lower middle market.


Investment  Strategy
Bay Capital seeks to invest $3 million to $10 million in historically profitable companies with strong management and a well-defined growth strategy.


Geographic Focus
Based in Providence, RI, Bay Capital invests primarily in businesses located east of the Mississippi River.








